comments: Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) has a resting hand on Mitchell's (UTA) shoulder that he neither extends nor delivers contact with.
At the end of the drive, Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) plants his left foot and then releases from the contact with Mitchell (UTA) before passing the ball.
Gobert (UTA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: The errant pass by Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) goes out of bounds.
There is no conclusive angle to see if Bogdanovic (UTA) steps out of bounds when he receives the pass.
At the end of the drive, Horford (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position on Conley (UTA) and makes clean ball contact to temporarily dislodge it.

Conley (UTA) is airborne when Horford (OKC) makes clean ball contact that causes Conley to temporarily fumble the ball. There should not be a jump ball whistle after Conley regains possession and comes back to the ground.
Horford (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in O'Neale's (UTA) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
At the end of the drive and before the gather, Bogdanovic (UTA) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Bazley (OKC).
Gobert (UTA) blocks Bazley's (OKC) shot attempt, any additional arm contact is deemed incidental.
During the rebound, Horford (OKC) and Mitchell (UTA) both go for the ball and any contact is deemed incidental.  The ball touches Mitchell last before going out of bounds.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) stops and plants his right foot releasing from the contact with Bogdanovic (UTA) on his step back jump shot attempt.
During the rebound, Mitchell (UTA) goes for the ball and slight contact to Hill's (OKC) arm occurs.  The contact does not affect Hill's ability to maintain full control of the ball.
After the made basket, Mitchell (UTA) never establishes himself out of bounds prior to the entry pass.
Horford (OKC) deflects the ball with his knee on the pass.
During the inbound, Bogdanovic (UTA) and Dort (OKC) engage and disengage off-ball.
Gobert (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Dort's (OKC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dort (OKC) jumps to the side of Mitchell (UTA) to legally contest his three-point attempt as Mitchell slightly extends his leg out and marginal contact with Dort occurs.
Hill (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in O'Neale's (UTA) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is connected with Mitchell (UTA) and releases from the contact without extending his arm or dislodging Mitchell from his legal guarding position.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) establishes his right foot as his pivot and steps through, he then releases the pass prior to his right foot landing.
Bogdanovic (UTA) establishes himself in a screening position in Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dort (OKC) moves slightly laterally into Mitchell's (UTA) path and marginal body contact occurs.  Mitchell is able to maintain his path to the basket and gather the ball cleanly.
Gobert (UTA) briefly places a hand to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) front and immediately removes during his drive to the basket.
Gobert (UTA) places a resting forearm to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) side after the release on his driving shot attempt.
